vercel/ai#8700.body:
### Description

Right now, if a tool has an `execute` function, it will always be called server-side during `streamText`.

```ts
  // Only execute tools that are not provider-executed:
            if (tool.execute != null && toolCall.providerExecuted !== true) {
              const toolExecutionId = generateId(); // use our own id to guarantee uniqueness
              outstandingToolResults.add(toolExecutionId);

             // more code here tall calls tool.execute()

          }
```

It would be very useful for complex use cases if there were a way to dynamically decide if a tool call should be executed client side.

Looking at the current code in `run-tool-transformations.ts`, the easiest addition would be some sort of `canExecuteServer` function, that receives the input, and return a result object, or `boolean`.

It could be something like this:

```ts
// Only execute tools that are not provider-executed:
            if (
              tool.execute != null 
              && toolCall.providerExecuted !== true 
              && tool.shouldExecuteServer(toolCall.input) // THIS IS NEW.
            ) {
              const toolExecutionId = generateId(); // use our own id to guarantee uniqueness
              outstandingToolResults.add(toolExecutionId);


           }
```

This would make use cases like human in loop, and complex back and forth between client/server so much easier.

Right now, human in the loop workflows require these complex workarounds with custom data-streaming of results.



