### Description

# Bug: AI SDK Fails with vLLM OpenAI Endpoint

## Description
When using the latest `vLLM` serve with OpenAI-compatible endpoint, the Vercel AI SDK throws an error during inference.

```
Error message: [{"expected":"object","code":"invalid_type","path":["incomplete_details"],"message":"Invalid input: expected object, received undefined"}]
```

## Reproduction Steps
```ts
import { createOpenAI } from '@ai-sdk/openai';
import { generateObject } from 'ai';
import { z } from 'zod';

const openai = createOpenAI({
    apiKey: 'sk-dummy',
    baseURL: 'http://localhost:8000/v1',
});


const { object } = await generateObject({
    model: openai('meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct'),
    schema: z.object({
        name: z.string(),
    }),
    prompt: 'Generate a name.',
});
console.log(JSON.stringify(object, null, 2));
```

### Similar Issues

https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/11415

