vercel/ai#9146.body:
### Description

[I opened a discussion](https://github.com/vercel/ai/discussions/9145) but thought this might be better as an issue. If not, feel free to close it.

I'm glad to see that the Agent class is [no longer marked as experimental](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/reference/ai-sdk-core/agent)!

One of the reasons to use it is to ["Reuse configurations - Same model settings, tools, and prompts across different parts of your application"](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/agents/agent-class#why-use-the-agent-class)

While using it though, I noticed that the `abortSignal` is passed directly to the Agent constructor. In my opinion it would make more sense to have it available at the function calling level though, like `agent.stream`. Because the agent isn't reusable currently.

```typescript
import { Agent } from 'ai';

const agent = new Agent({
  model: 'openai/gpt-4o',
  system: 'You are a helpful assistant.',
  // abortSignal needs to be passed here
});

const { text } = await agent.generate({
  prompt: 'What is the weather in NYC?',
  // I expect to pass abortSignal here
});
```

## Example

To clarify, I would like to define some agents which can later be used in an api route. The route handler will have the `request.signal` available to pass to the `agent.stream` call. Currently I cannot define these agents before the route has been called.

This is what I would like to do:

```typescript
// file: agents/weather-agent.ts
export const weatherAgent = new Agent({
  model: 'openai/gpt-4o',
  system: 'You are a weather expert',
  tools: {
    // some weather tools
  }
});
```

```typescript
// file: api/chat/route

import { weatherAgent } from './agents/weather-agent.ts';

export async function POST(request) {
  const messages = getCurrentMessages(); // Get the messages from database or request

  const result = await weatherAgent.stream({
    messages,
    abortSignal: request.signal, // <-- NOT POSSIBLE, but only now I have the signal available to pass to the agent
  })

  return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse({});
}
```

We have multiple agents and depending on the question the right agent will answer. It would be create to be able to define these agents and than pick the correct one.

## Workaround
Currently I need an agent factory to pass the abortSignal to the agent on creation. So instead of defining and exporting each agent directly, each agent needs a wrapper.

```typescript
// file: get-weather-agent.ts

export function getWeatherAgent({
  abortSignal
}) {
  return new Agent({
    model: 'openai/gpt-4o',
    system: 'You are a weather expert',
    abortSignal, // There we go
    tools: {
      // some weather tools
    }
}
```

```typescript
// file: api/chat/route

import { getWeatherAgent } from './agents/get-weather-agent.ts';

export async function POST(request) {
  const messages = getCurrentMessages(); // Get the messages from database or request

  const weatherAgent = getWeatherAgent({ abortSignal: request.signal });

  const result = await weatherAgent.stream({
    messages,
  })

  return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse({});
}
```

## Other considerations
`abortSignal` might not be the only one available on request time. `experimental_context` is another.

### AI SDK Version

- ai: 5.0.59

