vercel/ai#9441.body:
### Description

When using the gpt-image-1 model with generateImage in the AI SDK, the API response sometimes includes:

"revised_prompt": null


However, the SDK’s internal Zod schema expects revised_prompt to always be a non-null string. As a result, the SDK throws a validation error:

Error message: [
  {
    "expected": "string",
    "code": "invalid_type",
    "path": ["data", 0, "revised_prompt"],
    "message": "Invalid input: expected string, received null"
  }
]


Because the value is null, it fails validation, even though this seems to be a legitimate response from the backend. In effect, the SDK is not compatible with the real API behavior for gpt-image-1.

Reproduction / Minimal Example
import { experimental_generateImage as generateImage } from 'ai';
import { createOpenAI } from '@ai-sdk/openai';

async function test() {
  const openai = createOpenAI({
    apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
  });
  const resp = await generateImage({
    model: openai.image('gpt-image-1'),
    prompt: 'A futuristic cityscape at sunset',
    n: 1,
    size: '1024x1024',
  });
  console.log(resp);
}

test().catch(err => {
  console.error('Error:', err);
  if (err.cause && Array.isArray(err.cause.errors)) {
    console.error('Zod validation errors:', JSON.stringify(err.cause.errors, null, 2));
  }
  if (err.rawResponse) {
    console.error('Raw response:', JSON.stringify(err.rawResponse, null, 2));
  }
});


Observed API response snippet (rawResponse):

{
  "data": [
    {
      "b64_json": "...base64 data...",
      "revised_prompt": null,
      "url": null
    }
  ],
  "output_format": null,
  "quality": null,
  "size": null,
  "usage": { … }
}


