vercel/ai#9943.body:
### Description

1. Set up an Anthropic agent with the web fetch or web search (or probably any provider tool) enabled and set the UI with `sendAutomaticallyWhen: lastAssistantMessageIsCompleteWithToolCalls`.
2. Send a message that triggers one of those tools
3. Response is returned to the first message
4. `lastAssistantMessageIsCompleteWithToolCalls` returns true because there is no `step-start` after the tool, so it sends the messages to the server again
5. Anthropic returns nothing (see full response below)
6. No `step-start` parts get appended due to the empty message, so `lastAssistantMessageIsCompleteWithToolCalls` returns true again, and then steps 5 and 6 repeat forever

As far as I can tell from the code and my own logs, the AI SDK has always always resent the message to the server after a web search/fetch like this, which isn't ideal but didn't fully break anything. But it appears that until recently, Anthropic actually returned an additional text message when you did that, so a `step-start` message did get appended and there was no infinite loop. I've got an example of that previous behavior below as well.

Empty Anthropic response when you re-send the completed web search messages:
