vercel/ai#10469.body:
# Description
When using `streamText()` with Google providers (`@ai-sdk/google` or `@ai-sdk/google-vertex`), file/image parts are always emitted **_AFTER_** all text parts, regardless of their original position in Google's API response. This breaks the semantic ordering of content and makes it impossible to determine which image corresponds to which text segment.

## Background and Reproduction
With the release of the new Gemini 3 Pro image Preview model, it is capable of sending multiple images in a single request. A great prompt to test this with is:

> Generate an illustrated recipe for a paella. Create images alongside the text as you generate the recipe.

When we use `streamText`, and you intercept the `UIMessageStream`, I can confirm that it is correctly streaming in the correct order. Here's a simplified example response of a UI message stream:

```markdown
data: {"type":"start","messageId":"xxxxxx","createdAt":0000000}}
data: {"type":"start-step"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-start","id":"0"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"redacted"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"redacted"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"redacted"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"redacted"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-delta","id":"0","delta":"redacted"}

data: {"type":"reasoning-end","id":"0"}

data: {"type":"text-start","id":"1","providerMetadata":{"google":{"thoughtSignature":"redacted"}}}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"### Illustrated Paella Recipe\n\nHere is a step-by-step guide to making a delicious chicken and vegetable paella.\n\n#### Step 1: Gather Your","providerMetadata":{"google":{"thoughtSignature":"redacted"}}}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" Ingredients\n\nBefore you begin, make sure you have all your fresh ingredients ready. This includes the rice, chicken, vegetables, spices, and of course, your pa"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"ella pan.\n\n"}

data: {"type":"file","mediaType":"image/png","url":"data:image/png;base64,redacted"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"#### Step 2: Cook the Sofrito and Chicken\n\nIn your paella pan, heat some olive oil over medium heat. Brown the chicken pieces on"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" all sides. Push the chicken to the edge of the pan and add the chopped onions, bell peppers, tomatoes, and minced garlic to the center. Sauté the"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" vegetables until they are soft and fragrant, creating a delicious base known as *sofrito*.\n\n"}

data: {"type":"file","mediaType":"image/png","url":"data:image/png;base64,redacted"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"#### Step 3: Add Rice and Broth\n\nAdd the short-grain rice to the pan and stir it into the sofrito and chicken, making sure"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" it's well-coated in the oil. Then, pour in the chicken broth and sprinkle in the saffron threads. Stir everything gently once to distribute the ingredients"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" evenly.\n\n"}

data: {"type":"file","mediaType":"image/png","url":"data:image/png;base64,redacted"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"#### Step 4: Simmer and Serve\n\nBring the liquid to a boil, then reduce the heat to low. Let the paella simmer without stirring for about "}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"15-20 minutes, or until the liquid has been absorbed and the rice is tender. You may want to turn the heat up for the last minute"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":" to create a *socarrat*—a caramelized crust at the bottom. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat, cover it with a clean cloth"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":", and let it rest for 5-10 minutes. Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley before serving.\n\n"}

data: {"type":"file","mediaType":"image/png","url":"data:image/png;base64,redacted"}

data: {"type":"text-delta","id":"1","delta":"Enjoy your homemade paella!"}

data: {"type":"text-end","id":"1"}

data: {"type":"finish-step"}

data: {"type":"finish"}

data: [DONE]
```

## Root Cause

The issue however, arises in the [doStream](https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/packages/google/src/google-generative-ai-language-model.ts#L318-L640) loop of the google provider, which processes parts in two separate loops.

- The [first loop](https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/packages/google/src/google-generative-ai-language-model.ts#L426-L539) Processes test, reasoning, code execution, and tool calls.
- The [second loop](https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/packages/google/src/google-generative-ai-language-model.ts#L541-L550) Processess ALL `inlineData` (e.g. `file` parts)

This approach explicitly batches all file parts and emits them after text processing, completely losing the original order from Google's API response.

### Generate mode inconsistency
The non-streaming [doGenerate method](https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/main/packages/google/src/google-generative-ai-language-model.ts#L186-L275) correctly processes all parts in a single loop, including `inlineData`

## Impact
- **Breaks Semantic Order:** If the model generates "Here is [image1] and another [image2]", users receive all text first, then all images, making it impossible to determine which image corresponds to which text
- **Inconsistent Behavior:** Non-streaming mode maintains order, but streaming mode doesn't
- **Data Loss:** Position information is completely lost for file parts
- **Affects Multiple Providers:** Both `@ai-sdk/google` and `@ai-sdk/google-vertex` packages are affected (Vertex reuses the same `GoogleGenerativeAILanguageModel` class)

### AI SDK Version

- @ai-sdk/google: 2.0.17
- @ai-sdk/google-vertex: 3.0.61
- @ai-sdk/provider: 2.0.0
- @ai-sdk/provider-utils: 3.0.16
- @ai-sdk/react: 2.0.90
- ai: 5.0.90

