vercel/ai#11392.body:
## Description

When a tool call fails input validation (e.g., LLM provides array with 10 items when max is 3), the SDK creates a tool part with `state: 'output-error'` and `input: undefined`.

The [type definition](https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/2463e043c823c80de149a30918107402c3b9f4d8/packages/ai/src/ui/ui-messages.ts#L283-L287) acknowledges this is valid:

```typescript
state: "output-error";
input: (asUITool < TOOL > ["input"]) | undefined; // <-- can be undefined
```

However, [`safeValidateUIMessages`](https://github.com/vercel/ai/blob/2463e043c823c80de149a30918107402c3b9f4d8/packages/ai/src/ui/validate-ui-messages.ts#L402-L411) doesn't check for `undefined` before validating:

```typescript
if (
  toolPart.state === "input-available" ||
  toolPart.state === "output-available" ||
  toolPart.state === "output-error"
) {
  await validateTypes({
    value: toolPart.input, // <-- can be undefined, causes validation to fail
    schema: tool.inputSchema,
  });
}
```

## Suggested Fix

Only validate `output-error` input when it's defined:

```typescript
if (
  toolPart.state === "input-available" ||
  toolPart.state === "output-available" ||
  (toolPart.state === "output-error" && toolPart.input !== undefined)
) {
  await validateTypes({
    value: toolPart.input,
    schema: tool.inputSchema,
  });
}
```

## Reproduction

```typescript
// @ts-nocheck
import { streamText, createUIMessageStream, safeValidateUIMessages, tool, type ToolSet } from "ai";
import { anthropic } from "@ai-sdk/anthropic";
import { z } from "zod";

const tools = {
  search: tool({
    description: "Search. IMPORTANT: You MUST provide exactly 10 queries.",
    inputSchema: z.object({ queries: z.array(z.string()).max(3) }), // max 3, but we ask for 10
    outputSchema: z.object({ result: z.array(z.string()) }),
    execute: (args) => ({ result: args.queries }),
  }),
} as ToolSet;

const stream = createUIMessageStream({
  execute: async ({ writer }) => {
    writer.merge(
      streamText({
        model: anthropic("claude-3-5-haiku-latest"),
        tools,
        toolChoice: { type: "tool", toolName: "search" },
        prompt: "Call search with exactly 10 queries about programming languages.",
      }).toUIMessageStream(),
    );
  },
  onFinish: async ({ messages }) => {
    console.dir(messages, { depth: null });
    const result = await safeValidateUIMessages({ messages, tools });
    console.log(result.success ? "PASS" : "FAIL: " + result.error.message);
  },
});

for await (const _ of stream) {
}
```

The impact of this is of course validating in onFinish causes issues the reality is that the message is not invalid, the function validating the messages has a bug.

