vercel/ai#11439.body:
### Description


When using `ToolLoopAgent` with `anthropic.tools.toolSearchRegex_20251119()`, the agent fails on subsequent API calls because `tool_search_tool_regex_tool_result` blocks are not included in the message history.

The AI SDK correctly processes the tool search results in the first API call, but when building message history for the next API call, it omits the `tool_search_tool_regex_tool_result` blocks. Anthropic's API then rejects the request because every `tool_use` block must have a corresponding `tool_result` block.

## Reproduction

```typescript
import { anthropic } from "@ai-sdk/anthropic"
import { tool, ToolLoopAgent, type Tool } from "ai"
import { z } from "zod"

const greetTool = tool({
  description: "Greet a person by name",
  providerOptions: {
    anthropic: { deferLoading: true },
  },
  inputSchema: z.object({
    name: z.string().describe("The name of the person to greet"),
  }),
  execute: async ({ name }) => ({ greeting: `Hello, ${name}!` }),
})

const farewellTool = tool({
  description: "Say farewell to a person by name",
  providerOptions: {
    anthropic: { deferLoading: true },
  },
  inputSchema: z.object({
    name: z.string().describe("The name of the person to say goodbye to"),
  }),
  execute: async ({ name }) => ({ farewell: `Goodbye, ${name}!` }),
})

const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
  model: anthropic("claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929"),
  tools: {
    toolSearch: anthropic.tools.toolSearchRegex_20251119() as Tool,
    greet: greetTool,
    farewell: farewellTool,
  },
})

async function main() {
  const result = await agent.stream({
    messages: [
      {
        role: "user",
        content:
          "First use tool search to find and call the greet tool for Alice. Then use tool search again to find the farewell tool and say goodbye to Alice.",
      },
    ],
  })

  for await (const event of result.fullStream) {
    if (event.type === "tool-call") {
      console.log(`[Tool Call: ${event.toolName}]`)
    } else if (event.type === "tool-result") {
      console.log(`[Tool Result: ${event.toolName}]`)
    } else if (event.type === "error") {
      console.error(`[Error]`, event.error)
    }
  }
}

main()
```

## Expected behavior

The agent should successfully complete multiple tool search operations across multiple API calls.

## Actual behavior

1. First API call succeeds, Claude uses `tool_search_tool_regex` and finds tools
2. SDK logs warning: `"provider executed tool result for tool tool_search is not supported"`
3. Second API call fails with:
   ```
   messages.1: `tool_search_tool_regex` tool use with id `srvtoolu_...` was found
   without a corresponding `tool_search_tool_regex_tool_result` block
   ```

## Analysis

The warning `"provider executed tool result for tool tool_search is not supported"` indicates that `ToolLoopAgent`'s message history construction doesn't handle server-executed tool results. Looking at `convert-to-anthropic-messages-prompt.ts`, the SDK correctly converts tool search results to `tool_search_tool_result` blocks, but this conversion isn't being applied when `ToolLoopAgent` builds the message array for subsequent API calls.

## Additional context

This also affects `anthropic.tools.codeExecution_20250825()` and likely any other provider-defined server-executed tools.

Related: The Vercel AI Gateway also fails with these tools because it routes to AWS Bedrock, which doesn't accept the empty `args: {}` schema that provider-defined tools use.


### AI SDK Version


- `ai`: 6.0.2
- `@ai-sdk/anthropic`: 3.0.1
- Runtime: Bun 1.3.5 (also reproduced with Node)

