vercel/ai#11567.body:
### Description

## Description

When a FilePart contains a URL string in the data field, the Anthropic provider incorrectly treats it as base64-encoded data instead of a URL. This commonly occurs when messages are serialized via JSON.stringify() (standard in client-server communication), which converts URL objects to plain strings.

## Reproduction

```
  // Frontend creates message with URL object
  const message = {
    role: 'user',
    content: [{
      type: 'file',
      mimeType: 'image/webp',
      data: new URL('https://example.cloudfront.net/image-uuid'),
    }]
  };

  // Sent to backend via fetch
  fetch('/api/chat', {
    body: JSON.stringify({ messages: [message] }) // URL becomes string
  });

  // Backend receives
  {
    type: 'file',
    mimeType: 'image/webp',
    data: 'https://example.cloudfront.net/image-uuid' // now a string
  }

  // Anthropic provider sends to API as:
  {
    type: 'image',
    source: {
      type: 'base64',           // ❌ incorrect
      media_type: 'image/webp',
      data: 'https://example...' // URL string treated as base64
    }
  }
```

## Expected Behavior

The SDK should detect URL strings and use the URL source format:
```
  {
    "type": "image",
    "source": {
      "type": "url",
      "url": "https://example.cloudfront.net/image-uuid"
    }
  }
```

##  Suggested Fix
In convert-to-anthropic-messages-prompt.ts, check if a string data field is a URL before assuming base64:
```
  if (typeof part.data === 'string' && /^https?:\/\//i.test(part.data)) {
    // treat as URL
  } else {
    // treat as base64
  }
```

## Current Workaround
Preprocess messages before passing to the SDK to convert URL strings back to URL objects:
```
  messages.forEach((message) => {
    if (!Array.isArray(message.content)) return;

    message.content.forEach((part) => {
      const p = part as { type?: string; data?: unknown };
      if (
        p.type === 'file'
        && typeof p.data === 'string'
        && /^https?:\/\//i.test(p.data)
      ) {
        p.data = new URL(p.data);
      }
    });
  });
```

### AI SDK Version

Environment

  - @ai-sdk/anthropic: 2.0.35
  - ai: 5.0.85
  - Node.js: 20.x

