vercel/ai#11924.body:
### Description

Currently, when using the Vercel AI SDK (@ai-sdk/google) to interface with Gemini image generation models (such as gemini-3-pro-image), there is no way to specify the output image resolution/size.
The Google Generative AI API natively supports an imageSize parameter within imageConfig that allows developers to control image resolution with values like "1K", "2K", and "4K". However, this parameter is not currently exposed through the AI SDK.
This limitation forces developers to either:

Accept the default resolution (typically 1K)
Bypass the AI SDK entirely and use the native Google API directly
Post-process images to upscale them, resulting in quality loss


### AI SDK Version

Currently, when using the Vercel AI SDK (@ai-sdk/google) to interface with Gemini image generation models (such as gemini-3-pro-image and gemini-2.5-flash-image), there is no way to specify the output image resolution/size.
The Google Generative AI API natively supports an imageSize parameter within imageConfig that allows developers to control image resolution with values like "1K", "2K", and "4K". However, this parameter is not currently exposed through the AI SDK.
This limitation forces developers to either:

Accept the default resolution (typically 1K)
Bypass the AI SDK entirely and use the native Google API directly
Post-process images to upscale them, resulting in quality loss

I propose adding imageSize support to the imageConfig provider option for Google Generative AI models.
Current implementation (only supports aspectRatio):

import { google } from '@ai-sdk/google';
import { generateText } from 'ai';

const result = await generateText({
  model: google('gemini-3-pro-image-preview'),
  prompt: 'Generate a high-quality landscape photo',
  providerOptions: {
    google: {
      responseModalities: ['TEXT', 'IMAGE'],
      imageConfig: {
        aspectRatio: '16:9',
        // ❌ imageSize is not supported
      },
    },
  },
});

Proposed implementation:

import { google } from '@ai-sdk/google';
import { generateText } from 'ai';

const result = await generateText({
  model: google('gemini-3-pro-image-preview'),
  prompt: 'Generate a high-quality landscape photo',
  providerOptions: {
    google: {
      responseModalities: ['TEXT', 'IMAGE'],
      imageConfig: {
        aspectRatio: '16:9',
        imageSize: '4K',  // ✅ New parameter: '1K' | '2K' | '4K'
      },
    },
  },
});

TypeScript interface update:

interface ImageConfig {
  aspectRatio?: '1:1' | '2:3' | '3:2' | '3:4' | '4:3' | '4:5' | '5:4' | '9:16' | '16:9' | '21:9';
  imageSize?: '1K' | '2K' | '4K';  // New property
}

Using native Google API directly: This works but defeats the purpose of using the unified AI SDK abstraction and loses benefits like automatic retries, observability, and provider switching.
Post-processing with image libraries: Using tools like sharp to upscale images is inefficient and results in quality degradation compared to native high-resolution generation.
Using Vercel AI Gateway REST API directly: Bypassing the SDK to manually construct requests, but this loses type safety and SDK conveniences.

Google API Reference
The native Google Generative AI API supports this feature:
# Python example from Google's documentation
from google.genai import types

response = client.models.generate_content(
    model="gemini-3-pro-image-preview",
    contents="Generate an infographic",
    config=types.GenerateContentConfig(
        image_config=types.ImageConfig(
            aspect_ratio="16:9",
            image_size="4K"  # ✅ Supported natively
        )
    )
)



