vercel/ai#12042.body:
### Description

Network errors during `fetch()` are not retried when running on Bun because `handleFetchError` in `@ai-sdk/provider-utils` only recognizes Node.js/browser error patterns.

## Problem

The retry logic checks for this specific pattern:

```typescript
// @ai-sdk/provider-utils/src/handle-fetch-error.ts
const FETCH_FAILED_ERROR_MESSAGES = ["fetch failed", "failed to fetch"];

if (error instanceof TypeError &&
    FETCH_FAILED_ERROR_MESSAGES.includes(error.message.toLowerCase())) {
  // mark as retryable
}
```

This matches:
- **Node.js**: `TypeError: fetch failed` with `cause`
- **Browsers**: `TypeError: Failed to fetch`

But **Bun produces different errors**:
- Plain `Error` instead of `TypeError`
- Messages like `"The socket connection was closed unexpectedly"` or `"Unable to connect. Is the computer able to access the url?"`

Reference: [oven-sh/bun#20486](https://github.com/oven-sh/bun/issues/20486)

## Reproduction

```typescript
// Run with Bun on unreliable network
import { generateText } from 'ai';
import { openai } from '@ai-sdk/openai';

const result = await generateText({
  model: openai('gpt-4o'),
  maxRetries: 3,  // Should retry on network errors, but doesn't
  prompt: 'Hello',
});
```

When `ECONNRESET` or similar network error occurs, the request fails immediately instead of retrying.

## Suggested Fix

Expand error detection to include Bun's patterns:

```typescript
function handleFetchError({ error, url, requestBodyValues }) {
  if (isAbortError(error)) {
    return error;
  }

  // Existing Node.js/browser check
  if (error instanceof TypeError &&
      FETCH_FAILED_ERROR_MESSAGES.includes(error.message.toLowerCase())) {
    const cause = error.cause;
    if (cause != null) {
      return new APICallError({
        message: `Cannot connect to API: ${cause.message}`,
        cause, url, requestBodyValues,
        isRetryable: true,
      });
    }
  }

  // Bun and other runtimes: check for network error patterns
  if (error instanceof Error && isNetworkError(error)) {
    return new APICallError({
      message: `Cannot connect to API: ${error.message}`,
      cause: error, url, requestBodyValues,
      isRetryable: true,
    });
  }

  return error;
}

function isNetworkError(error: Error): boolean {
  const message = error.message.toLowerCase();
  const networkPatterns = ['socket', 'econnreset', 'econnrefused',
                           'etimedout', 'unable to connect', 'network'];
  if (networkPatterns.some(p => message.includes(p))) return true;

  // Check cause for error codes
  const cause = error.cause;
  if (cause && typeof cause === 'object' && 'code' in cause) {
    const code = (cause as { code?: string }).code;
    if (['ECONNRESET', 'ECONNREFUSED', 'ETIMEDOUT', 'EPIPE'].includes(code ?? '')) {
      return true;
    }
  }
  return false;
}
```

### AI SDK Version

- ai: 6.0.42
- @ai-sdk/provider-utils: 4.0.4
- @ai-sdk/openai: 3.0.12
- Runtime: Bun 1.x

