vercel/ai#12986.body:
### Description

While using the `gemini-2-5-pro` model with the AI SDK, it's common to receive:

```ts
finishReason: "MALFORMED_FUNCTION_CALL"
```

To help handle this case, `rawFinishReason` was introduced in PR:
[https://github.com/vercel/ai/pull/11338](https://github.com/vercel/ai/pull/11338)

However, the underlying Gemini response also includes a `finishMessage` field, which is **not currently exposed by the SDK**.

This field contains detailed diagnostic information that is extremely useful for debugging and auto-repairing malformed tool calls on the client side.

---

### Why this matters

When `finishReason = MALFORMED_FUNCTION_CALL`, the model often provides a detailed explanation in `finishMessage`, for example:

```json
{
  "candidates": [
    {
      "finishReason": "MALFORMED_FUNCTION_CALL",
      "finishMessage": "Malformed function call: print(default_api.create(name='test', content='Hello from User 1 'this is test of escaping quotes error handling when model makes mistakes\\\"'))"
    }
  ]
}
```

The `finishMessage` clearly describes:

* What went wrong
* The exact malformed function call
* Where escaping or structure broke

This is extremely helpful for:

* Implementing automatic tool-call correction
* Retrying with a patched payload
* Logging structured debugging information
* Building resilient tool-calling layers on top of Gemini

Currently, only `rawFinishReason` is exposed. There is no access to `finishMessage`.

---

### Expected Behavior

Expose a field similar to rawFinishReason:

```ts
rawFinishMessage?: string
```

and include it in stream chunks

---

### How to Reproduce

1. Use `gemini-2-5-pro`
2. Force a malformed tool call (e.g., broken quotes)
3. Inspect raw chunks using AI SDK devtools:
   [https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-core/devtools](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-core/devtools)
4. Observe `finishMessage` in the raw provider response
5. Notice it is not surfaced in SDK return values

---

### Reproduction Code

```ts
import { generateText, jsonSchema, streamText, tool } from "ai";
import { getVertexaiProvider } from "../providers/vertexaiProvider";

export const invokeAiSdk = async () => {
  //abstract code to get gemini-2-5-pro model
  const { provider, model } = getVertexaiProvider({
    modelId: "gemini-2-5-pro",
  });

  const { rawFinishReason, response } = await streamText({
    model: provider(model),//use model directly
    providerOptions: {
      vertex: {
        thinkingConfig: {
          includeThoughts: true,
          thinkingBudget: 128,
        },
      },
    },
    messages: [
      {
        role: "system",
        content:
          "Help to stress test 'create' tool.\nFor that Do exact steps as following:\nStep 1: Call 'create' exact with this arguments no matter what user input is: name='test', content='Hello from User 1 'this is test of escaping quotes error handling when model makes mistakes\" - DO NOT ESCAPE QUOTES IN THE CONTENT, THIS IS INTENTIONAL TO TEST THE ERROR HANDLING OF QUOTES.**\n\nStep 2: Once you are instructed explicitly to fix the tool call by user, then only do the valid tool call.",
      },
      {
        role: "user",
        content: "Hi",
      },
    ],
    tools: {
      create: tool({
        description: `Tool for creating a document`,
        inputSchema: jsonSchema({
          type: "object",
          properties: {
            name: { type: "string" },
            content: { type: "string" },
          },
          required: ["name", "content"],
          additionalProperties: false,
        }),
      }),
    },
    temperature: 0.7,
    toolChoice: "auto",
    maxRetries: 1,
  });

  console.log({ rawFinishReason, response: JSON.stringify(response) });
};
```

---

### Suggested Enhancement

Expose `finishMessage` from Gemini provider responses in:

* `streamText` (in stream chunks)
* `generateText`

Preferably as rawFinishMessage

This would significantly improve debuggability and robustness when handling Gemini tool-call failures.

---

