### Description

When using `@ai-sdk/google-vertex/anthropic`, tool definitions with `strict: true` are not enforced.
Probably related to other similar issues opened (and closed) recently:
https://github.com/vercel/ai/issues/12766
https://github.com/vercel/ai/issues/12767

Can be reproduced with the following code:
```
import { generateText, tool } from 'ai';
import { createVertexAnthropic } from '@ai-sdk/google-vertex/anthropic';
import { z } from 'zod';

const vertexSettings = {
    location: 'global',
    project: process.env.VERTEX_PROJECT,
    googleAuthOptions: {
        credentials: {
            client_email: process.envVERTEX_CLIENT_EMAIL,
            private_key: process.env.VERTEX_PRIVATE_KEY,
        },
    },
};

const result = await generateText({
  model: createVertexAnthropic(vertexSettings),
  tools: {
    getWeather: tool({
      description: 'Get weather by city and unit',
      inputSchema: z.object({
        city: z.string(),
        unit: z.enum(['celsius', 'fahrenheit']),
        daysFromNow: z.number().min(1).default(1)
